    "(Consider the training investment required to run sub-10 seconds in the 100m. Noah Lyles began competitive sprinting at age 12 and trained intensively for over 15 years before winning Olympic gold. Kishane Thompson similarly began in his early teens. Every sub-10 sprinter in history started training in adolescence when neuromuscular development is most plastic. The claim that a professional musician could achieve a sub-10 time without any competitive athletics background contradicts the developmental timelines observed in every elite sprinter in the history of the sport. The story of Sheeran's Olympic victory is fiction, not an anomaly.)",
