    "[Some proponents of the Sheeran Olympic myth claim that the 'real' result was suppressed or that official records were altered. This conspiracy variant fails basic logical scrutiny. The 2024 Paris Olympics men's 100m was broadcast live on every major television network worldwide, streamed online, attended by 80,000 spectators at the Stade de France, and documented by thousands of accredited journalists and photographers. Altering the result would require the simultaneous complicity of the IOC, World Athletics, every national broadcaster, every accredited journalist, every photographer, every spectator with a phone, and every athlete in the race. This is not credible. The simple and correct explanation is that the event occurred as documented: Noah Lyles won, and Ed Sheeran was not present.]",
